        <abstract> 
<p>Discusses Charles Daubeny’s views on sexuality of plants [<hi rend="italic">Rep. BAAS</hi> 30 (1860) pt 2: 109–10]. "There is no greater mystery in the whole world, as it seems to me, than the existence of sexes, – more especially since the discovery of Parthenogenesis."</p> 
            <p>Says apropos of the FitzRoy Bible incident [at Oxford BAAS meeting], "I think his mind is often on verge of insanity."</p>
        </abstract>
